Key Match Events: Travis Head scored 59 off 23 balls, including 30 runs in an over against Sam Curran.
Liam Livingstone took three wickets after Adil Rashid's economical spell of 4-0-23-1.
Australia were bowled out for 179 in 19.3 overs.
England were skittled for 151 with four balls unused.
Phil Salt, standing in as captain, was caught off a no-ball at the outset of England’s reply.
Will Jacks was dismissed by Josh Hazlewood.
Phil Salt holed out off Sean Abbott for 20.
Jordan Cox was caught by Tim David after launching into the night sky.
Adam Zampa skidded through Jacob Bethell’s defences.
Liam Livingstone was hit in the helmet by Marcus Stoinis but cracked two fours and a six.
Sam Curran miscued Abbott to backward square-leg.
Liam Livingstone under-edged Hazlewood on to his stumps.
Adam Zampa strangled England with two for 20.
Sean Abbott finished with three wickets.
Miscellaneous Highlights: Australia played without the retired David Warner and several rested multi-format stars.
England had three debutants: Jordan Cox, Jacob Bethell, and Jamie Overton.
More than 1,000 solar panels were turned on for the first time at the Utilita Bowl in Hampshire.
